.SH NAME
drm_sysfs_hotplug_event \- generate a DRM uevent
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_sysfs_hotplug_event
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Send a uevent for the DRM device specified by \fIdev\fP.  Currently we only
set HOTPLUG=1 in the uevent environment, but this could be expanded to
deal with other types of events.

Any new uapi should be using the \fBdrm_sysfs_connector_status_event\fP
for uevents on connector status change.
